<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4895] Thread local TableDescriptor#referencedColumnMap is not removed from app threads when Derby is shut down</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4895</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; This has been seen to cause error messages in TomCat, cf. this quote from a mail on derby-user:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-user/201011.mbox/%3C7800E37B639BC345BC2AB40980B7C529180FB525@MERCMBX03R.na.SAS.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-user/201011.mbox/%3C7800E37B639BC345BC2AB40980B7C529180FB525@MERCMBX03R.na.SAS.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; SEVERE: The web application &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;/MyApp&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; created a ThreadLocal with key of type [org.apache.derby.iapi.sq\&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; l.dictionary.TableDescriptor$1] (value &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;org.apache.derby.iapi.sql.dictionary.TableDescriptor$1@d133a3&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;)\&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;  and a value of type &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;java.util.WeakHashMap&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; (value [{=&lt;/p&gt;
{1, 2, 3, 4}
&lt;p&gt;, =null, =null}]) but failed to remo\&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ve it when the web application was stopped. This is very likely to create a memory leak.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
